# Default Apps 2024

All the favorite people I follow online have posted their "default apps" 2024 posts. So, under unspoken peer pressure, I decided to do the same.

## Operating Systems

*   **Work:** MacOS
*   **Home server:** Linux Mint
*   **Home general:** Windows 10
*   **Phone:** Android

## Internet

*   **Web browser (work):** Chrome
*   **Web browser (home and phone):** Firefox and Fennec
*   **Gemini browser:** Amfora (command line), Lagrange (GUI) and Geopard (Linux)
*   **IRC client:** Weechat (command line), HexChat (GUI), and Revolution IRC (phone)
*   **XMPP client (phone):** Monocles and Conversations
*   **Mastodon client (phone):** Tusky
*   **Lemmy client (phone):** Voyager
*   **RSS clent (phone):** Feedly
*   **Email provider:** Proton Mail, Gmail (for historical reasons)
*   **VPN:** Proton VPN
*   **Cloud storage:** pCloud, Proton Drive, and Google Drive (for Google Docs)
*   **Torrent client:** Deluge
*   **File transfer:** FileZilla
*   **Static site generator:** Quarto

## Productivity

*   **Calendar:** Gmail (personal) and Outlook (work)
*   **ToDo (phone):** Tasks
*   **Notes:** Simplenote, Standard Notes, Obsidian

## Utility

*   **File explorer (phone):** Cx File Explorer
*   **Voice recorder (phone):** Samsung's Voice Recorder
*   **Speech to text translator:** Vibe (Linux)
*   **Phone to computer sync:** FolderSync (Android app)
*   **Bookmark:** Raindrop (Firefox and Chrome extension)
*   **Password manager:** Bitwarden
*   **Ether pad:** [https://pad.disroot.org](https://pad.disroot.org)
*   **Editor:** NVIM (Linux, MacOS), Visual Studio Code (Linux, MacOS), and RStudio (MacOS)
*   **Terminal:** iTerm (MacOS), Termius (Phone)
*   **Server monitoring:** ServerBox (Android app)
*   **E-books:** ReadEra Premium (phone), Kindle (phone), Hoopla (public library books), Caliber (personal collection management)
*   **Bible:** ESV, Our Daily Bread
*   **Dictionary:** WordWeb (phone)
*   **PDF manipulation:** PDF Arranger and Okular
*   **Image manipulation and illustration:** Gimp and Inkscape
*   **Rsync:** Grsync (Linux)
*   **Remote disk mount:** Gigolo (Linux)
  
## Outdoors

*   **Hiking:** AllTrails
*   **Survival:** Survival Manual (offline)
*   **Geocaching:** Geocaching (official app)
*   **Parks:** MD DNR, Recreation.gov, and NPS
*   **Weather:** Weather Bug
*   **Fishing:** Fishing Spots, Fishbrain
*   **Birding:** Merlin Bird ID
*   **Maps:** Google Maps and OsmAnd+

## Audio and Video

*   **Plex:** music and movies (home server)
*   **Media player:** VLC (every where)
*   **Radio:** Jazz Radio (phone)
*   **Streaming:** Prime Video, Spotify (free)
*   **Video editing:** Kdenline and HandBrake
*   **Audio tagging:** MusicBrainz Picard

## Ham Radio

*   **Ham radio dashboard:** [https://rohitfarmer.com/ham-dash](https://rohitfarmer.com/ham-dash)
*   **Logger:** Google Sheet

